
Overview of noun replacement

The noun replacement has 6 senses (first 4 from tagged texts)
                                    
1. (4) replacement, replacing -- (the act of furnishing an equivalent person or thing in the place of another; "replacing the star will not be easy")
2. (2) surrogate, alternate, replacement -- (someone who takes the place of another person)
3. (2) substitution, permutation, transposition, replacement, switch -- (an event in which one thing is substituted for another; "the replacement of lost blood by a transfusion of donor blood")
4. (1) substitute, replacement -- (a person or thing that takes or can take the place of another)
5. refilling, replenishment, replacement, renewal -- (filling again by supplying what has been used up)
6. successor, replacement -- (a person who follows next in order; "he was President Lincoln's successor")
